      "note": "the 2024 nominations, under new owners",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "The Color Purple",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Sean's biggest snub: left out of Best Musical or Comedy, a category the hosts thought it was built for. Two acting noms survive (Fantasia Barrino, Danielle Brooks), but the picture's absence dents its Oscar case."
        },
        {
          "title": "Air",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "The film that took The Color Purple's musical/comedy slot; Matt Damon nominated for lead. Viola Davis's supporting omission bugs Sean, who calls her the best part of the movie."
        },
        {
          "title": "Anatomy of a Fall",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Best Motion Picture, Drama nominee; the hosts note its strong overall haul."
        },
        {
          "title": "Killers of the Flower Moon",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Drama nominee with seven nominations, but Sean predicts it gets shut out on the night."
        },
        {
          "title": "Maestro",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Best Motion Picture, Drama nominee."
        },
        {
          "title": "Oppenheimer",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Eight nominations; Sean's pick to win the most Globes, edging Poor Things."
        },
        {
          "title": "Past Lives",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Five nominations, including a Best Director nod for Celine Song, a surprise that pleases the hosts. They puzzle over how it qualified as a non-English-language contender."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Zone of Interest",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Drama nominee; both hosts glad to see it recognized."
        },
        {
          "title": "American Fiction",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Best Musical or Comedy nominee."
        },
        {
          "title": "Barbie",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Most-nominated film of the year, partly on the strength of three Best Original Song nods. Amanda dreads a Billie Eilish ballad win but champions 'Dance the Night.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "The Holdovers",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Musical or Comedy nominee, but no Best Director nod for Alexander Payne (a Globes darling with seven career noms) has Sean wondering if it's a softer contender than assumed."
        },
        {
          "title": "May December",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Musical or Comedy nominee. Amanda's gender-split anecdote: the men in her life love it, the women are more divided."
        },
        {
          "title": "Poor Things",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Seven nominations. Amanda recounts Golden Globe voters at Venice loudly panning it before a screening."
        },
        {
          "title": "All of Us Strangers",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Not nominated for picture but Andrew Scott landed a Best Actor nod; the hosts see an outside Best Picture path amid a big FYC weekend."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Boy and the Heron",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Weekend box-office No. 1 and well reviewed; floated as a possible animated Best Picture contender over Spider-Verse."
        },
