    {
      "kind": "interview",
      "heading": "In conversation",
      "note": "Julia Roberts and Sam Esmail on the Netflix apocalypse",
      "guest": "Julia Roberts and Sam Esmail on",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Leave the World Behind",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Esmail wrote and directed this adaptation of Rumaan Alam's novel, with Roberts as the prickly Amanda, Mahershala Ali as G.H., Ethan Hawke, and Myha'la (whose character he changed from G.H.'s wife to his daughter to seed doubt). Esmail inverts the disaster genre: characters front and center, catastrophe kept at a distance and deliberately unexplained. Set pieces (the beached ship, the deer, the driverless Teslas) are his inventions, not the book's. Roberts describes daytime-only reading because it scared her, and a mortifying dance scene with Ali. The film ends on young Rose finally watching the 'Friends' series finale, an ending Esmail knew would divide audiences and stood by."
        }
      ]
    }
